  <Header Context="NGAMS" Name="ngamsServer.xml" Release="1.0" Revision="@(#) $Id: NgamsCfg1.ORACLE.RAID5.subscriber.xml,v 1.1 2009/11/26 15:47:20 awicenec Exp $" Source="ngast@eso.org" Type="NGAMS-CONFIGURATION">
    <Description>
      Configuration used for the deployment NGAS servers. This configuration assumes
      RAID volumes to be pre-mounted. There is no replication configured. The configuration
      is compatible with the Oracle client configuration (tnsnames.ora) and connects to the
      RAC cluster in failover mode.
      *NOTES*: 
               The RAID volumes have to be mounted on /NGAS/volume* at 
                 boot time. NGAS does not do the mounting with this 
                 configuration.
               There is no mirroring or caching configured yet.
               The DB pool is disabled.
    </Description>
  </Header>

